+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016dT1kaiz8TmPm6gh5CUMTn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully explored and read the entire codebase. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n## Complete Codebase Structure\n\n### **Configuration Files**\n\n**package.json**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-debug-nightmare\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Event-driven order processing system — hard debugging benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**tsconfig.json** - TypeScript configuration targeting ES2022 with Node16 module resolution\n\n**vitest.config.ts** - Vitest test runner configuration\n\n---\n\n## Source Code Files\n\n### **1. Event Bus System** (`/workspace/src/events/`)\n\n#### `src/events/types.ts`\nDefines event interfaces and constants:\n- `OrderEvent` base interface with `orderId` and `timestamp`\n- `OrderCreatedEvent` - triggered when order is created\n- `OrderCancelledEvent` - triggered on cancellation\n- `OrderRefundedEvent` - triggered on refund\n- `PaymentChargedEvent` - payment processing event\n- `StockReservedEvent` - inventory reservation\n- `ORDER_EVENTS` constant object with event names (CREATED, CONFIRMED, CANCELLED, REFUNDED, PAYMENT_CHARGED, STOCK_RESERVED, STOCK_RELEASED, NOTIFICATION_SENT)\n\n#### `src/events/bus.ts`\nEvent bus implementation with:\n- `EventHandler` type for handler functions\n- `EventBus` class with methods:\n  - `on(event, handler)` - register handler\n  - `off(event, handler)` - unregister handler\n  - `emit(event, data)` - emit event to all handlers\n  - `clear()` - clear all handlers\n- Global module-level handler registry shared across EventBus instances\n\n---\n\n### **2. Order Service** (`/workspace/src/orders/`)\n\n#### `src/orders/repository.ts`\nIn-memory order storage with:\n- `OrderStatus` type ('pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded')\n- `OrderItem` interface with productId, quantity, unitPrice\n- `Order` interface with full order details\n- `OrderRepository` class with:\n  - `create(order)` - create order\n  - `findById(id)` - retrieve by ID\n  - `update(id, updates)` - update order\n  - `findByCustomer(customerId)` - find all orders for customer\n  - `findByStatus(status)` - find orders by status\n  - `clear()` - clear store\n\n#### `src/orders/service.ts`\nOrder business logic with:\n- `REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS = 30` constant\n- `OrderService` class with dependencies on OrderRepository, EventBus, and BillingService\n- Methods:\n  - `createOrder()` - creates order, emits CREATED event, charges payment, emits CONFIRMED\n  - `cancelOrder()` - validates confirmation, emits CANCELLED event\n  - `refundOrder()` - issues refund within 30-day window, throws error if expired\n  - `getOrder()` - retrieve single order\n  - `getOrdersByCustomer()` - retrieve customer's orders\n\n---\n\n### **3. Inventory Management** (`/workspace/src/inventory/`)\n\n#### `src/inventory/repository.ts`\nStock tracking with:\n- `StockRecord` interface with productId, available, reserved quantities\n- `InventoryRepository` class with:\n  - `setStock(productId, available)` - set available quantity\n  - `getStock(productId)` - retrieve stock record\n  - `reserve(productId, quantity)` - reserve stock (checks availability)\n  - `release(productId, quantity)` - release reserved stock\n  - `clear()` - clear store\n\n#### `src/inventory/service.ts`\nEvent-driven inventory service with:\n- `InventoryService` class with dependencies on InventoryRepository and EventBus\n- `registerHandlers()` - registers handlers for ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED and CANCELLED\n- `handleOrderCreated()` - reserves stock for all items, rolls back on partial failure\n- `handleOrderCancelled()` - releases reserved stock\n- `setStock()` and `getStock()` - convenience methods\n\n---\n\n### **4. Billing & Payment** (`/workspace/src/billing/`)\n\n#### `src/billing/calculator.ts`\nPrice calculation utility:\n- `PriceBreakdown` interface with subtotal, discountAmount, taxAmount, total\n- `calculateOrderTotal()` function:\n  - Calculates subtotal from items\n  - Applies percentage discount\n  - Calculates tax on discounted amount\n  - Returns breakdown with proper rounding\n\n#### `src/billing/service.ts`\nPayment processing with:\n- `PaymentRecord` interface with orderId, amount, method, status, processedAt\n- `BillingService` class with dependencies on EventBus and NotificationService\n- `registerHandlers()` - registers handlers for STOCK_RESERVED and REFUNDED events\n- `handleStockReserved()` - emits PAYMENT_CHARGED event\n- `chargePayment()` - charges order, records payment, sends confirmation\n- `issueRefund()` - refunds payment, emits REFUNDED event\n- `getPayment()` - retrieve payment record\n- `clear()` - clear payments\n\n---\n\n### **5. Notifications** (`/workspace/src/notifications/`)\n\n#### `src/notifications/service.ts`\nNotification management with:\n- `NotificationRecord` interface with type, orderId, message, sentAt\n- `NotificationService` class with:\n  - Template system for confirmation, cancellation, refund messages\n  - `sendConfirmation()` - send order confirmation\n  - `sendCancellation()` - send cancellation notice\n  - `sendRefundNotice()` - send refund notification\n  - `getSentNotifications()` - retrieve all sent notifications\n  - `clear()` - clear sent history\n\n---\n\n### **6. Main Export** (`/workspace/src/index.ts`)\nBarrel file exporting all public APIs from the system\n\n---\n\n## Test Files\n\n### **`tests/events.test.ts`**\nEventBus tests:\n- emits events to registered handlers\n- supports multiple handlers for same event\n- doesn't fire handlers for different events\n- removes handlers with off()\n- clears all handlers\n\n### **`tests/orders.test.ts`**\nOrderService and OrderRepository tests:\n- creates order and confirms it (status + total calculation)\n- reserves stock when order created\n- cancels confirmed orders\n- releases stock on cancellation\n- refuses to cancel non-confirmed orders\n- refunds cancelled orders within 30 days\n- allows refund on exactly day 30\n- rejects refund after 30-day window\n- repository create/retrieve operations\n- update preserves other fields\n- finds orders by customer\n\n### **`tests/inventory.test.ts`**\nInventoryService tests:\n- reserves stock on order.created event\n- throws when stock insufficient\n- rolls back partial reservations on failure\n- releases stock on order.cancelled event\n- handles concurrent orders independently\n\n### **`tests/billing.test.ts`**\nBilling and calculator tests:\n- `calculateOrderTotal()` tests:\n  - calculates total with no discount/tax\n  - applies percentage discount before tax\n  - handles multiple items with discount and tax\n  - rounds correctly for penny-edge amounts\n- `BillingService` tests:\n  - charges payment and records it\n  - sends confirmation notification on charge\n  - issues refund and updates payment status\n  - sends refund notification\n\n### **`tests/notifications.test.ts`**\nNotificationService tests:\n- sends order confirmation\n- sends cancellation notice\n- sends refund notice\n- tracks all sent notifications\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Summary\n\nThis is a **modular event-driven order processing system** with:\n\n1. **Event Bus** - Central pub/sub mechanism for decoupling services\n2. **Order Service** - Orchestrates order lifecycle (create, confirm, cancel, refund)\n3. **Inventory Service** - Event listener that reserves/releases stock\n4. **Billing Service** - Event listener that handles payments and refunds\n5. **Notification Service** - Templates-based notification sender\n6. **Repositorie